- QTD Regional crack spreads (CRKSM21T) averaged \(\sim\) US\(13.59/bbl (2Q25 \sim\) US \(11.87/bbl) vs. ALD's QTD share price +14%, VEA flat, and ASX200 Energy +7%.- QTD Refining Margin Markers averaged \(\sim\) A\(10.75c/L for ALD's Lytton (2Q25 \sim\) A\(9.02c/L), and \sim\) A\(9.15c/L for VEA's Geelong (2Q25 \sim\) A\(7.48c/L).- QTD Petrol margins averaged \sim\) A\(17.62c/L (2Q25 \sim\) A\(17.42c/L) and diesel margins \sim\) A\(15.59c/L (2Q25 \sim\) A\(19.45c/L).- EV sales were 7% of Jul-25 Australia vehicle sales, +7% vs. pcp, and hybrids were 22%, +8 vs. pcp (source: VFacts), on plug-in hybrid uptake.- The Federal Government's Fuel Security Services Payment (FFSP) review is underway, which we think could be a positive catalyst.

What's in the price?

ALD's share price is up \(14\%\) so far this quarter vs. the ASX200 up \(5\%\) and the ASX Energy index up \(7\%\) . We estimate ALD's share price equates to 2029- 50 FCF growth of \(- 0.8\%\) p.a. vs. Vis. Alpha cons.

On 14 August 2025, ALD announced its acquisition of the EG Ampol business for A\(1.1b. We have not incorporated this transaction in our base case estimates, as we await ACCC and regulatory approvals. However, if completed, we think the price looks balanced (7.8x EV/EBITDA pre- synergies) and we view the execution risk as manageable. ALD targets mid- 26 completion.
VEA's share price is flat QTD. We estimate VEA's share price equates to 2029- 50 FCF growth of \(- 6.0\%\) vs. Vis. Alpha cons., which incorporates VEA growth targets.

In 1H25, VEA completed 9 OTR store conversions at \(\sim \mathsf{A}\mathsf{S}1.5\mathsf{m}\) capex/store, and VEA anticipates \(\sim 36\) store conversions in 2H25, with VEA's preference for landlord funding for major building works. VEA continues to target \(\sim 80 - 100\) store conversions pa.

VEA is in commercial discussions for its proposed LNG import facility in Geelong, targeting FID in early 2026. VEA moved into FEED in Dec- 24, and received environmental approval from the Victorian Government in May- 25.

Keep EW. Our VEA valuation equates to 12mf EV/EBITDA of 7.0x (5- year average of 7.1x, post- AASB16). At a \(\sim 56\%\) RCOP NPAT payout ratio (50- 70% policy), our estimates equate to a \(4.3\%\) fully franked yield. Estimated 1- year TSR for VEA is 2nd quartile in our Australia Energy coverage, with higher execution risk and gearing keeping us EW.

ALD is our preferred refining/convenience stock, with an undemanding valuation, strong balance sheet, and catalysts in energy security policy, refining margin recovery, and rate cuts and lower fuel prices supporting convenience, all providing
We see a slow but steady recovery in travel, and we think crude markets and China anti- involution policy could provide refining margin support.
Tobacco industry developments heighten social license risk.

We view ALD's measured investments in new energy (EV charging, hydrogen mobility, sustainable aviation fuel) as longer- term positives, if successful, as well as prudent market intelligence for the ongoing business.

We think VEA's retail acquisitions (Coles Express, On- The- Run) are logical and add scale and scope, but we remain wary of execution, funding and integration risks.
